M_LOC[ 448] = "Ānanda, there are these eight liberations.<br>What eight?<br>Having physical form, they see visions.<br>This is the first liberation.<br>Not perceiving form internally, they see visions externally.<br>This is the second liberation.<br>They’re focused only on beauty.<br>This is the third liberation.<br>Going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, they enter and remain in the dimension of infinite space.<br>This is the fourth liberation.<br>Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, they enter and remain in the dimension of infinite consciousness.<br>This is the fifth liberation.<br>Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, they enter and remain in the dimension of nothingness.<br>This is the sixth liberation.<br>Going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, they enter and remain in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.<br>This is the seventh liberation.<br>Going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, they enter and remain in the cessation of perception and feeling.<br>This is the eighth liberation.<br>These are the eight liberations.";
M_LOC[ 449] = "Ānanda, this one time, when I was first awakened, I was staying near Uruvelā at the goatherd’s banyan tree on the bank of the Nerañjarā River.";
M_LOC[ 450] = "Then Māra the wicked approached me, stood to one side, and said:";
M_LOC[ 451] = "‘Sir, may the Blessed One now become fully extinguished! May the Holy One now become fully extinguished! Now is the time for the Buddha to become fully extinguished.’";
M_LOC[ 452] = "layman disciples …";
M_LOC[ 453] = "laywoman disciples who are competent, educated, assured, learned.";
M_LOC[ 454] = "Not until my spiritual life is successful and prosperous, extensive, popular, widespread, and well proclaimed wherever there are gods and humans.’";
M_LOC[ 455] = "Today, just now at the Cāpāla shrine Māra the Wicked approached me once more with the same request, reminding me of my former statement, and saying that those conditions had been fulfilled.";
M_LOC[ 456] = "When he had spoken, I said to Māra:";
M_LOC[ 457] = "‘Relax, Wicked One. The final extinguishment of the Realized One will be soon.";
M_LOC[ 458] = "Three months from now the Realized One will finally be extinguished.’";
M_LOC[ 459] = "So today, just now at the Cāpāla tree shrine, mindful and aware, I surrendered the life force.”";
M_LOC[ 460] = "20. The Appeal of Ānanda";
M_LOC[ 461] = "Ānanda, this one time I was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain.";
M_LOC[ 462] = "There I said to you:";
M_LOC[ 463] = "‘Ānanda, Rājagaha is lovely, and so is the Vulture’s Peak.";
M_LOC[ 464] = "Whoever has developed and cultivated the four bases of psychic power—made them a vehicle and a basis, kept them up, consolidated them, and properly implemented them—may, if they wish, live on for the eon or what’s left of the eon.";
M_LOC[ 465] = "";
M_LOC[ 466] = "";
M_LOC[ 467] = "Then the Buddha went to the assembly hall, where he sat on the seat spread out<br>and addressed the mendicants:<br>“So, mendicants, having carefully memorized those things I have taught you from my direct knowledge, you should cultivate, develop, and make much of them so that this spiritual practice may last for a long time. That would be for the welfare and happiness of the people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.<br>And what are those things I have taught from my direct knowledge?<br>They are: the four kinds of mindfulness meditation, the four right efforts, the four bases of psychic power, the five faculties, the five powers, the seven awakening factors, and the noble eightfold path.<br>These are the things I have taught from my direct knowledge. Having carefully memorized them, you should cultivate, develop, and make much of them so that this spiritual practice may last for a long time. That would be for the welfare and happiness of the people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.”<br>Then the Buddha said to the mendicants:<br>“Come now, mendicants, I say to you all:";
M_LOC[ 468] = "";
M_LOC[ 469] = "";
M_LOC[ 470] = "Having given it up, I’ll depart;<br>I’ve made a refuge for myself.";
M_LOC[ 471] = "Diligent and mindful,<br>be of good virtues, mendicants!";
M_LOC[ 472] = "With well-settled thoughts,<br>take good care of your minds.<br>Whoever meditates diligently";
M_LOC[ 473] = "";
M_LOC[ 474] = "giving up transmigration through rebirths,";
M_LOC[ 475] = "will make an end to suffering.”";
M_LOC[ 476] = "21. The Elephant Look";
M_LOC[ 477] = "Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Vesālī for alms.";
M_LOC[ 478] = "Then, after the meal, on his return from alms-round, he turned his whole body, the way that elephants do, to look back at Vesālī. He said to Venerable Ānanda:";
M_LOC[ 479] = "“Ānanda, this will be the last time the Realized One sees Vesālī.";
M_LOC[ 480] = "these things have been understood<br>by Gotama the renowned.<br>And so the Buddha, having insight,";
M_LOC[ 481] = "";
M_LOC[ 482] = "The teacher made an end of suffering,";
M_LOC[ 483] = "seeing clearly, he is extinguished.”";
M_LOC[ 484] = "And while staying there, too, he often gave this Dhamma talk to the mendicants:";
M_LOC[ 485] = "“Such is ethics, such is immersion, such is wisdom.";
M_LOC[ 486] = "When immersion is imbued with ethics it’s very fruitful and beneficial.";
M_LOC[ 487] = "When wisdom is imbued with immersion it’s very fruitful and beneficial.";
M_LOC[ 488] = "When the mind is imbued with wisdom it is rightly freed from the defilements, namely,";
M_LOC[ 489] = "the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.”";
M_LOC[ 490] = "22. The Four Great References";
M_LOC[ 491] = "When the Buddha had stayed in Bhaṇḍagāma as long as he wished, he addressed Ānanda,";
M_LOC[ 492] = "“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to Hatthigāma.”…";
M_LOC[ 493] = "";
M_LOC[ 494] = "After the Buddha had eaten Cunda’s meal, he fell severely ill with bloody dysentery, struck by dreadful pains, close to death.<br>But he endured with mindfulness and situational awareness, without worrying.<br>Then he addressed Ānanda,<br>“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to Kusinārā.”<br>“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied.";
M_LOC[ 495] = "I’ve heard that after eating<br>the meal of Cunda the smith,";
M_LOC[ 496] = "the wise one fell severely ill,<br>with pains, close to death.";
M_LOC[ 497] = "A severe sickness attacked the Teacher";
M_LOC[ 498] = "who had eaten the pork on the turn.";
M_LOC[ 499] = "While still purging the Buddha said:";
M_LOC[ 500] = "“I’ll go to the citadel of Kusinārā.”";
M_LOC[ 501] = "24. Bringing a Drink";
M_LOC[ 502] = "Then the Buddha left the road and went to the root of a tree, where he addressed Ānanda,";
M_LOC[ 503] = "“Please, Ānanda, fold my outer robe in four and spread it out for me. I am tired and will sit down.”";
M_LOC[ 504] = "“Yes, sir,” replied Ānanda, and did as he was asked.";
