M_LOC[ 716] = "Then King Mahāsudassana left the great foyer and entered the golden chamber, where he sat on the golden couch.";
M_LOC[ 717] = "He meditated spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way he spread a heart full of love above, below, across, everywhere, all around, to everyone in the world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.";
M_LOC[ 718] = "King Mahāsudassana had 84,000 cities, with the royal capital of Kusāvatī foremost.";
M_LOC[ 719] = "He had 84,000 palaces, with the Palace of Principle foremost.";
M_LOC[ 720] = "He had 84,000 chambers, with the great foyer foremost.";
M_LOC[ 721] = "He had 84,000 couches made of gold, silver, ivory, and hardwood. They were spread with woollen covers—shag-piled, pure white, or embroidered with flowers—and spread with a fine deer hide, with a canopy above and red pillows at both ends.";
M_LOC[ 722] = "He had 84,000 bull elephants with gold adornments and banners, covered with gold netting, with the royal bull elephant named Sabbath foremost.";
M_LOC[ 723] = "‘Sire, you have 84,000 cities, with the royal capital of Kusāvatī foremost.";
M_LOC[ 724] = "Arouse desire for these! Take an interest in life!’";
M_LOC[ 725] = "‘For a long time, my queen, you have spoken to me with loving, desirable, pleasant, and agreeable words.";
M_LOC[ 726] = "And yet in my final hour, your words are undesirable, unpleasant, and disagreeable!’";
M_LOC[ 727] = "‘Then how exactly, Your Majesty, am I to speak to you?’";
M_LOC[ 728] = "‘Like this, my queen:";
M_LOC[ 729] = "“Sire, we must be parted and separated from all we hold dear and beloved. Don’t pass away with concerns. Such concern is suffering, and it’s criticized.";
M_LOC[ 730] = "Sire, you have 84,000 cities, with the royal capital of Kusāvatī foremost.";
M_LOC[ 731] = "Give up desire for these! Take no interest in life!”’";
M_LOC[ 732] = "See, Ānanda! All those conditioned phenomena have passed, ceased, and perished.";
M_LOC[ 733] = "So impermanent are conditions,";
M_LOC[ 734] = "so unstable are conditions,";
M_LOC[ 735] = "having arisen, they cease;";
M_LOC[ 736] = "their stilling is true bliss.”";
M_LOC[ 737] = "Long Discourses 18";
M_LOC[ 738] = "With Janavasabha";
M_LOC[ 739] = "1. Declaring the Rebirths of People From Nādika and Elsewhere";
M_LOC[ 740] = "So I have heard.";
M_LOC[ 741] = "At one time the Buddha was staying at Nādika in the brick house.";
M_LOC[ 742] = "Now at that time the Buddha was explaining the rebirths of devotees all over the nations; the Kāsis and Kosalans, Vajjis and Mallas, Cetīs and Vaṁsas, Kurus and Pañcālas, Macchas and Sūrasenas:";
M_LOC[ 743] = "“This one was reborn here, while that one was reborn there.";
M_LOC[ 744] = "Over fifty devotees in Nādika have passed away having ended the five lower fetters. They’ve been reborn spontaneously, and will be extinguished there, not liable to return from that world.";
M_LOC[ 745] = "Soon after Ānanda had left, the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Nādika for alms.";
M_LOC[ 746] = "He wandered for alms in Nādika. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he washed his feet and entered the brick house. He paid heed, paid attention, and concentrated wholeheartedly on the fate of Magadhan devotees, and sat on the seat spread out, thinking,";
M_LOC[ 747] = "“I shall know their destiny, where they are reborn in the next life.”";
M_LOC[ 748] = "And he saw where they had been reborn.";
M_LOC[ 749] = "Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat. Emerging from the brick house, he sat on the seat spread out in the shade of the porch.";
M_LOC[ 750] = "Seven from here, seven from there—<br>fourteen transmigrations in all.";
M_LOC[ 751] = "That’s how many past lives";
M_LOC[ 752] = "I can recollect.";
M_LOC[ 753] = "For a long time I’ve known that I won’t be reborn in the underworld, but that I still hope to become a once-returner.’";
M_LOC[ 754] = "Sir, it was more than a few days ago—on the fifteenth day sabbath on the full moon day at the entry to the rainy season—when all the gods of the Thirty-Three were sitting together in the Hall of Justice.";
M_LOC[ 755] = "A large assembly of gods was sitting all around, and the Four Great Kings were there.";
M_LOC[ 756] = "The Great King Dhataraṭṭha was seated to the east, facing west, in front of his gods.";
M_LOC[ 757] = "The Great King Virūḷhaka was seated to the south, facing north, in front of his gods.";
M_LOC[ 758] = "The Great King Virūpakkha was seated to the west, facing east, in front of his gods.";
M_LOC[ 759] = "The Great King Vessavaṇa was seated to the north, facing south, in front of his gods.";
M_LOC[ 760] = "When the gods of the Thirty-Three have a gathering like this, that is how they are seated.";
M_LOC[ 761] = "After that come our seats.";
M_LOC[ 762] = "Sir, those gods who had been recently reborn in the company of the Thirty-Three after leading the spiritual life under the Buddha outshone the other gods in beauty and glory.";
M_LOC[ 763] = "The gods of the Thirty-Three were uplifted and overjoyed at that, full of rapture and happiness, saying,";
M_LOC[ 764] = "“The heavenly hosts swell, while the demon hosts dwindle!”";
M_LOC[ 765] = "Seeing the joy of those gods, Sakka, lord of gods, celebrated with these verses:";
M_LOC[ 766] = "“The gods rejoice—";
M_LOC[ 767] = "the Thirty-Three with their Lord—";
M_LOC[ 768] = "revering the Realized One,";
M_LOC[ 769] = "and the natural excellence of the teaching;";
M_LOC[ 770] = "and seeing the new gods,";
M_LOC[ 771] = "";
M_LOC[ 772] = "";
M_LOC[ 773] = "";
M_LOC[ 774] = "";
M_LOC[ 775] = "";
M_LOC[ 776] = "";
M_LOC[ 777] = "";
M_LOC[ 778] = "";
M_LOC[ 779] = "";
M_LOC[ 780] = "";
M_LOC[ 781] = "";
M_LOC[ 782] = "";
M_LOC[ 783] = "";
M_LOC[ 784] = "When one is speaking,<br>all the forms speak.";
M_LOC[ 785] = "When one sits in silence,";
M_LOC[ 786] = "they all remain silent.";
M_LOC[ 787] = "that the one on their seat";
M_LOC[ 788] = "is the only one to speak.";
M_LOC[ 789] = "The Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra merged into one corporeal form. Then he sat on the couch of Sakka, lord of gods, and addressed the gods of the Thirty-Three:";
M_LOC[ 790] = "6. Developing the Bases of Psychic Power";
M_LOC[ 791] = "All the ascetics and brahmins in the past,";
M_LOC[ 792] = "future,";
M_LOC[ 793] = "or present who wield the many kinds of psychic power do so by developing and cultivating these four bases of psychic power.";
M_LOC[ 794] = "Next, take someone whose coarse physical, verbal, and mental processes have not died down.<br>After some time they hear the teaching of the noble ones, properly attend to how it applies to them, and practice accordingly.<br>Their coarse physical, verbal, and mental processes die down.<br>That gives rise to pleasure, and more than pleasure, happiness,<br>like the joy that’s born from gladness.<br>This is the second opportunity for achieving happiness.<br>Next, take someone who doesn’t truly understand what is skillful and what is unskillful,<br>what is blameworthy and what is blameless, what should be cultivated and what should not be cultivated, what is inferior and what is superior, and what is on the side of dark and the side of bright.<br>After some time they hear the teaching of the noble ones, properly attend to how it applies to them, and practice accordingly.<br>They truly understand what is skillful and what is unskillful, and so on.";
M_LOC[ 795] = "";
M_LOC[ 796] = "";
M_LOC[ 797] = "";
M_LOC[ 798] = "";
M_LOC[ 799] = "";
M_LOC[ 800] = "Whoever has experiential confidence in the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha, and has the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones; and whoever is spontaneously reborn, and is trained in the teaching; in excess of 2,400,000 such Magadhan devotees have passed away having ended three fetters. They’re stream-enterers, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.<br>And there are once-returners here, too.<br>And as for other people";
M_LOC[ 801] = "";
M_LOC[ 802] = "I couldn’t even number them,";
M_LOC[ 803] = "for fear of speaking falsely.”";
M_LOC[ 804] = "That is the topic on which Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra spoke. And while he was speaking on that topic, this thought came to the great king Vessavaṇa,";
M_LOC[ 805] = "“It’s incredible, it’s amazing! That there should be such a magnificent Teacher, and such a magnificent exposition of the teaching! And that such achievements of high distinction should be made known!”";
M_LOC[ 806] = "And then Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra, knowing what the great king Vessavaṇa was thinking, said to him,";
M_LOC[ 807] = "Long Discourses 19<br>The Great Steward<br>So I have heard.";
M_LOC[ 808] = "";
M_LOC[ 809] = "";
M_LOC[ 810] = "";
M_LOC[ 811] = "";
M_LOC[ 812] = "";
M_LOC[ 813] = "";
M_LOC[ 814] = "";
M_LOC[ 815] = "";
M_LOC[ 816] = "";
M_LOC[ 817] = "";
M_LOC[ 818] = "";
M_LOC[ 819] = "";
M_LOC[ 820] = "";
M_LOC[ 821] = "The gods of the Thirty-Three were even more uplifted and overjoyed at that, full of rapture and happiness, saying,";
M_LOC[ 822] = "‘The heavenly hosts swell, while the demon hosts dwindle!’";
M_LOC[ 823] = "2. Eight Genuine Praises";
M_LOC[ 824] = "Seeing the joy of those gods, Sakka, lord of gods, addressed them,";
M_LOC[ 825] = "‘Gentlemen, would you like to hear eight genuine praises of the Buddha?’";
M_LOC[ 826] = "Also, the Buddha has clearly described the practice that leads to extinguishment for his disciples. And extinguishment and the practice come together,";
M_LOC[ 827] = "as the waters of the Ganges come together and converge with the waters of the Yamuna.";
M_LOC[ 828] = "Also, the Buddha has gained companions, both trainees who are practicing, and those with defilements ended who have completed their journey.";
M_LOC[ 829] = "The Buddha is committed to the joy of solitude, but doesn’t send them away.";
M_LOC[ 830] = "I don’t see any Teacher, past or present, so committed to the joy of solitude, apart from the Buddha.";
M_LOC[ 831] = "These are the eight genuine praises of the Buddha proffered by Sakka.<br>Hearing them, the gods of the Thirty-Three were even more uplifted and overjoyed.<br>Then some gods thought,<br>‘If only four fully awakened Buddhas might arise in the world and teach the Dhamma, just like the Blessed One!<br>That would be for the welfare and happiness of the people, out of compassion for the world, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans!’<br>Other gods thought,<br>‘Let alone four fully awakened Buddhas; if only three fully awakened Buddhas,<br>or two fully awakened Buddhas might arise in the world and teach the Dhamma, just like the Blessed One!<br>That would be for the welfare and happiness of the people, out of compassion for the world, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans!’<br>When they said this, Sakka said,";
M_LOC[ 832] = "";
M_LOC[ 833] = "";
M_LOC[ 834] = "With clear and peaceful minds,<br>they stood by their own seats.";
M_LOC[ 835] = "Then in the northern quarter a magnificent light arose and radiance appeared, surpassing the glory of the gods.<br>Then Sakka, lord of gods, addressed the gods of the Thirty-Three,<br>‘As indicated by the signs—light arising and radiance appearing—Brahmā will appear. For this is the precursor for the appearance of Brahmā, namely light arising and radiance appearing.’";
M_LOC[ 836] = "As indicated by the signs,<br>Brahmā will appear.";
M_LOC[ 837] = "For this is the sign of Brahmā:";
M_LOC[ 838] = "a light vast and great.";
M_LOC[ 839] = "3. On Sanaṅkumāra";
M_LOC[ 840] = "When Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra appears to the gods of the Thirty-Three, he does so after manifesting in a solid corporeal form,";
M_LOC[ 841] = "for the gods of the Thirty-Three aren’t able to see a Brahmā’s normal appearance.";
M_LOC[ 842] = "When Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra appears to the gods of the Thirty-Three, he outshines the other gods in beauty and glory,";
M_LOC[ 843] = "as a golden statue outshines the human form.";
M_LOC[ 844] = "When Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra appears to the gods of the Thirty-Three, not a single god in that assembly greets him by bowing down or rising up or inviting him to a seat.";
M_LOC[ 845] = "They all sit silently on their couches with their joined palms raised, thinking,";
M_LOC[ 846] = "‘Now Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra will sit on the couch of whatever god he chooses.’";
M_LOC[ 847] = "And the god on whose couch Brahmā sits is overjoyed and brimming with happiness,";
M_LOC[ 848] = "like a king on the day of his coronation.";
M_LOC[ 849] = "That is the topic on which Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra spoke.";
M_LOC[ 850] = "And while he was speaking on that topic, his voice had eight qualities: it was clear, comprehensible, charming, audible, rounded, undistorted, deep, and resonant.";
M_LOC[ 851] = "He makes sure his voice is intelligible as far as the assembly goes, but it doesn’t extend outside the assembly.";
M_LOC[ 852] = "When someone has a voice like this, they’re said to have the voice of Brahmā.";
M_LOC[ 853] = "Then the gods of the Thirty-Three said to Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra,";
M_LOC[ 854] = "‘Good, Great Brahmā! Knowing this, we rejoice.";
M_LOC[ 855] = "And there are the eight genuine praises of the Buddha spoken by Sakka—";
M_LOC[ 856] = "knowing them, too, we rejoice.’";
M_LOC[ 857] = "4. Eight Genuine Praises";
M_LOC[ 858] = "Then Brahmā said to Sakka,";
M_LOC[ 859] = "";
M_LOC[ 860] = "";
M_LOC[ 861] = "";
M_LOC[ 862] = "‘What do the gods of the Thirty-Three think about the extent of the Buddha’s great wisdom?";
M_LOC[ 863] = "Once upon a time, there was a king named Disampati.";
M_LOC[ 864] = "He had a brahmin high priest named the Steward.";
M_LOC[ 865] = "Disampati’s son was the prince named Reṇu,";
M_LOC[ 866] = "while the Steward’s son was the student named Jotipāla.";
M_LOC[ 867] = "There were Reṇu the prince, Jotipāla the student, and six other aristocrats; these eight became friends.";
M_LOC[ 868] = "In due course the brahmin Steward passed away.";
M_LOC[ 869] = "At his passing, King Disampati lamented,";
M_LOC[ 870] = "“At a time when I have relinquished all my duties to the brahmin Steward and amuse myself, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation, he passes away!”";
M_LOC[ 871] = "Mithila for the Videhas;<br>Campā was made for the Aṅgas;";
M_LOC[ 872] = "and Varanasi for the Kāsīs:";
M_LOC[ 873] = "these were laid out by the Steward.";
M_LOC[ 874] = "Then those six aristocrats were delighted with their respective gains, having achieved all they wished for,";
M_LOC[ 875] = "Reṇu and the two Dhataraṭṭhas:<br>these are the seven Bhāratas.";
M_LOC[ 876] = "The first recitation section is finished.";
M_LOC[ 877] = "6.2. A Good Reputation";
M_LOC[ 878] = "Then the six aristocrats approached the Great Steward and said,";
M_LOC[ 879] = "“Steward, just as you are King Reṇu’s friend, dear, beloved, and cherished,";
M_LOC[ 880] = "";
M_LOC[ 881] = "";
M_LOC[ 882] = "";
M_LOC[ 883] = "";
M_LOC[ 884] = "";
M_LOC[ 885] = "";
M_LOC[ 886] = "";
M_LOC[ 887] = "";
M_LOC[ 888] = "Not knowing, I ask—";
M_LOC[ 889] = "how am I to know who you are?”";
M_LOC[ 890] = "All the gods know me thus,";
M_LOC[ 891] = "and so you should know me, Steward.”";
M_LOC[ 892] = "Sir, I ask you to please accept";
M_LOC[ 893] = "these gifts of hospitality.”";
M_LOC[ 894] = "I grant you the opportunity<br>to ask whatever you desire—";
M_LOC[ 895] = "about welfare and benefit in this life,";
M_LOC[ 896] = "or happiness in lives to come.”";
M_LOC[ 897] = "Then the Great Steward thought,";
M_LOC[ 898] = "about things one may learn from another.";
M_LOC[ 899] = "Standing on what, training in what";
M_LOC[ 900] = "may a mortal reach the deathless Brahmā realm?”";
M_LOC[ 901] = "“He among men, O brahmin, has given up possessions,";
M_LOC[ 902] = "become one, compassionate,";
M_LOC[ 903] = "free from the stench of decay, and refraining from sex.";
M_LOC[ 904] = "Standing on that, training in that";
M_LOC[ 905] = "a mortal may reach the deathless Brahmā realm.”";
M_LOC[ 906] = "“Sir, I understand what ‘giving up possessions’ means.";
M_LOC[ 907] = "";
M_LOC[ 908] = "I don’t understand, so tell me, wise one:";
M_LOC[ 909] = "wrapped in what do people stink,";
M_LOC[ 910] = "headed for hell, shut out of the Brahmā realm?”";
M_LOC[ 911] = "“Anger, lies, fraud, and deceit,";
M_LOC[ 912] = "miserliness, vanity, jealousy,";
M_LOC[ 913] = "desire, stinginess, harassing others,";
M_LOC[ 914] = "greed, hate, pride, and delusion—";
M_LOC[ 915] = "those bound to such things have the stench of decay;";
M_LOC[ 916] = "they’re headed for hell, shut out of the Brahmā realm.”";
M_LOC[ 917] = "“As I understand what you say about the stench of decay, it’s not easy to quell while living at home.";
M_LOC[ 918] = "I shall go forth from the lay life to homelessness!”";
M_LOC[ 919] = "“Please do so, Steward, at your convenience.”";
M_LOC[ 920] = "6.4. Informing King Reṇu";
M_LOC[ 921] = "you must learn how to rule,<br>for I no longer care for my ministry.”<br>“If you’re lacking any pleasures,";
M_LOC[ 922] = "";
M_LOC[ 923] = "I’ll protect you from any harm,<br>for I command the nation’s army.";
M_LOC[ 924] = "You are my father, I am your son!<br>O Steward, please don’t leave!”<br>“I’m lacking no pleasures,";
M_LOC[ 925] = "";
M_LOC[ 926] = "";
M_LOC[ 927] = "";
M_LOC[ 928] = "hearing which you would abandon<br>our house and all our people?”<br>“Before entering this retreat,";
M_LOC[ 929] = "";
M_LOC[ 930] = "I kindled the sacred flame,<br>strewn about with kusa grass.";
M_LOC[ 931] = "But then Brahmā appeared to me,<br>the Eternal Youth from the Brahmā realm.";
M_LOC[ 932] = "He answered my question,";
M_LOC[ 933] = "hearing which I no longer care for lay life.”";
M_LOC[ 934] = "“I have faith, O Steward,";
M_LOC[ 935] = "We will follow your example,<br>Steward, be my Teacher!<br>Like a gem of beryl—";
M_LOC[ 936] = "";
M_LOC[ 937] = "that’s how pure we shall live,<br>in the Steward’s dispensation.";
M_LOC[ 938] = "If the Steward is going forth from the lay life to homelessness, we shall do so too. Your destiny shall be ours.”";
M_LOC[ 939] = "6.5. Informing the Six Aristocrats";
M_LOC[ 940] = "Then the Great Steward went to the six aristocrats and said,";
M_LOC[ 941] = "“Sirs, please now find another high priest to manage the affairs of state for you.";
M_LOC[ 942] = "I wish to go forth from the lay life to homelessness.";
M_LOC[ 943] = "exert yourselves, being strong,<br>and possessing the power of patience.";
M_LOC[ 944] = "This path is the straight path,<br>this path is supreme.";
M_LOC[ 945] = "Guarded by the good, the true teaching";
M_LOC[ 946] = "leads to rebirth in the Brahmā realm.”";
M_LOC[ 947] = "“Well then, sir, please wait for seven years.";
M_LOC[ 948] = "When seven years have passed, we shall go forth with you.”";
M_LOC[ 949] = "“Seven years is too long, sirs. I cannot wait that long.";
M_LOC[ 950] = "";
M_LOC[ 951] = "";
M_LOC[ 952] = "";
M_LOC[ 953] = "";
M_LOC[ 954] = "";
M_LOC[ 955] = "";
M_LOC[ 956] = "";
M_LOC[ 957] = "When a week had passed, the Great Steward shaved off his hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness.<br>And when he had gone forth, the seven anointed aristocrat kings, the seven brahmins with seven hundred initiates, the forty equal wives, and many thousands of aristocrats, brahmins, householders, and many harem women shaved off their hair and beards, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness.<br>Escorted by that assembly, the Great Steward wandered on tour among the villages, towns, and capital cities.<br>And at that time, whenever he arrived at a village or town, he was like a king to kings, like Brahmā to brahmins, like a deity to householders.<br>And whenever people sneezed or tripped over<br>they’d say:<br>“Homage to the Great Steward! Homage to the high priest for the seven!”";
M_LOC[ 958] = "And the Great Steward meditated spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, he spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.<br>He meditated spreading a heart full of compassion …<br>rejoicing …<br>equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, he spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.<br>And he taught his disciples the path to rebirth in the company of Brahmā.<br>Those of his disciples who completely understood the Great Steward’s instructions,";
M_LOC[ 959] = "";
M_LOC[ 960] = "";
M_LOC[ 961] = "";
M_LOC[ 962] = "";
M_LOC[ 963] = "That is what the Buddha said.";
M_LOC[ 964] = "Delighted, the fairy Pañcasikha approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. He bowed and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before vanishing right there.";
M_LOC[ 965] = "Long Discourses 20";
M_LOC[ 966] = "The Great Congregation";
M_LOC[ 967] = "So I have heard.";
M_LOC[ 968] = "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near Kapilavatthu in the Great Wood, together with a large Saṅgha of around five hundred mendicants, all of whom were perfected ones.";
M_LOC[ 969] = "And most of the deities from ten solar systems had gathered to see the Buddha and the Saṅgha of mendicants.";
M_LOC[ 970] = "Then four deities of the Pure Abodes, aware of what was happening, thought:";
M_LOC[ 971] = "“Why don’t we go to the Buddha and each recite a verse in his presence?”";
M_LOC[ 972] = "Like a charioteer who has taken the reins,";
M_LOC[ 973] = "the astute ones protect their senses.”";
M_LOC[ 974] = "Then another deity recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence:";
M_LOC[ 975] = "They live pure and immaculate,";
M_LOC[ 976] = "the young dragons tamed by the seer.”";
M_LOC[ 977] = "Then another deity recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence:";
M_LOC[ 978] = "After giving up this human body,";
M_LOC[ 979] = "they swell the hosts of gods.”";
M_LOC[ 980] = "1. The Gathering of Deities";
M_LOC[ 981] = "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants:";
M_LOC[ 982] = "“Mendicants, most of the deities from ten solar systems have gathered to see the Realized One and the mendicant Saṅgha.";
M_LOC[ 983] = "there, in mountain caves,<br>resolute and composed,";
M_LOC[ 984] = "dwell many like lonely lions,<br>who have mastered their fears.";
M_LOC[ 985] = "Their minds are bright and pure,<br>clear and undisturbed.”<br>The teacher knew that over five hundred";
M_LOC[ 986] = "";
M_LOC[ 987] = "";
M_LOC[ 988] = "";
M_LOC[ 989] = "";
M_LOC[ 990] = "Knowledge manifested in them,<br>seeing those non-human beings.";
M_LOC[ 991] = "Some saw a hundred,<br>a thousand, even seventy thousand,<br>while some saw a hundred thousand";
M_LOC[ 992] = "";
M_LOC[ 993] = "But some saw an endless number";
M_LOC[ 994] = "spread out in every direction.";
M_LOC[ 995] = "And all that was known";
M_LOC[ 996] = "and distinguished by the Seer.";
M_LOC[ 997] = "I shall extol them for you,<br>with lyrics in proper order.";
M_LOC[ 998] = "There are seven thousand spirits,";
M_LOC[ 999] = "earth-gods of Kapilavatthu.";
M_LOC[1000] = "They’re powerful and brilliant,";
M_LOC[1001] = "From the Himalayas there are six thousand";
M_LOC[1002] = "spirits of different colors.";
M_LOC[1003] = "They’re powerful and brilliant,";
M_LOC[1004] = "From Sātāgira there are three thousand";
M_LOC[1005] = "spirits of different colors.";
M_LOC[1006] = "They’re powerful and brilliant,";
M_LOC[1007] = "so beautiful and glorious.";
M_LOC[1008] = "Rejoicing, they’ve come forth";
M_LOC[1009] = "to the meeting of mendicants in the wood.";
M_LOC[1010] = "And thus there are sixteen thousand";
M_LOC[1011] = "spirits of different colors.";
M_LOC[1012] = "They’re powerful and brilliant,";
M_LOC[1013] = "so beautiful and glorious.";
M_LOC[1014] = "Attended by more than";
M_LOC[1015] = "a hundred thousand spirits,";
M_LOC[1016] = "King Dhataraṭṭha rules<br>the eastern quarter.";
M_LOC[1017] = "Lord of the fairies,";
M_LOC[1018] = "he’s a great king, glorious.";
M_LOC[1019] = "And he has many mighty sons";
M_LOC[1020] = "all of them named Inda.";
M_LOC[1021] = "King Virūḷha rules<br>the southern quarter.";
M_LOC[1022] = "Lord of the goblins,";
M_LOC[1023] = "he’s a great king, glorious.";
M_LOC[1024] = "And he has many mighty sons";
M_LOC[1025] = "all of them named Inda.";
M_LOC[1026] = "King Virūpakkha rules<br>the western quarter.";
M_LOC[1027] = "Lord of the dragons,";
M_LOC[1028] = "he’s a great king, glorious.";
M_LOC[1029] = "And he has many mighty sons";
M_LOC[1030] = "all of them named Inda.";
M_LOC[1031] = "King Kuvera rules<br>the northern quarter.";
M_LOC[1032] = "Lord of spirits,";
M_LOC[1033] = "he’s a great king, glorious.";
M_LOC[1034] = "And he has many mighty sons";
M_LOC[1035] = "all of them named Inda.";
M_LOC[1036] = "Dhataraṭṭha in the east,<br>Virūḷhaka to the south,";
M_LOC[1037] = "Virūpakkha to the west,<br>and Kuvera in the north.";
M_LOC[1038] = "These Four Great Kings,<br>all around in the four quarters,<br>stood there dazzling";
M_LOC[1039] = "";
M_LOC[1040] = "Their deceitful bondservants came,";
M_LOC[1041] = "so treacherous and crafty—";
M_LOC[1042] = "And Candana and Kāmaseṭṭha,<br>Kinnughaṇḍu and Nighaṇḍu,";
M_LOC[1043] = "Panāda and Opamañña,";
M_LOC[1044] = "and Mātali, the god’s charioteer.";
M_LOC[1045] = "as well as Pañcasikha,<br>Timbaru, and Suriyavaccasā.";
M_LOC[1046] = "These and other kings there were,";
M_LOC[1047] = "the fairies with their kings.";
M_LOC[1048] = "Rejoicing, they’ve come forth";
M_LOC[1049] = "to the meeting of mendicants in the wood.";
M_LOC[1050] = "From Yamunā the Dhataraṭṭha<br>dragons came, so glorious.";
M_LOC[1051] = "And Erāvaṇa the great dragon<br>also came to the meeting in the wood.";
M_LOC[1052] = "Those who seize the dragon kings by force—<br>divine, twice-born birds with piercing vision—<br>swoop down to the wood from the sky;";
M_LOC[1053] = "";
M_LOC[1054] = "But the dragon kings remained fearless,<br>for the Buddha kept them safe from the phoenixes.";
M_LOC[1055] = "Introducing each other with gentle words,<br>the dragons and phoenixes took the Buddha as their refuge.";
M_LOC[1056] = "Defeated by Vajirahattha,<br>the demons live in the ocean.";
M_LOC[1057] = "They’re brothers of Vāsava,<br>powerful and glorious.<br>There’s the terrifying Kālakañjas,";
M_LOC[1058] = "";
M_LOC[1059] = "Vepacitti and Sucitti,<br>Pahārāda with Namuci,";
M_LOC[1060] = "and a hundred of Bali’s sons,<br>all named after Veroca.<br>Bali’s army armed themselves";
M_LOC[1061] = "";
M_LOC[1062] = "";
M_LOC[1063] = "The gods of Water and Earth,<br>and Fire and Wind came there.<br>The Varuṇa and Vāruṇa gods,";
M_LOC[1064] = "";
M_LOC[1065] = "";
M_LOC[1066] = "";
M_LOC[1067] = "";
M_LOC[1068] = "";
M_LOC[1069] = "";
M_LOC[1070] = "The gods living on the moon came,<br>with the Moon before them.<br>The gods living on the sun came,";
M_LOC[1071] = "";
M_LOC[1072] = "And with the stars before them<br>came the silly gods of clouds.<br>And Sakka came, the stronghold-giver,";
M_LOC[1073] = "";
M_LOC[1074] = "";
M_LOC[1075] = "";
M_LOC[1076] = "";
M_LOC[1077] = "Then came the Sahabhū gods,<br>blazing like a crested flame;";
M_LOC[1078] = "and the Ariṭṭhakas and Rojas too,<br>and the gods hued blue as flax.";
M_LOC[1079] = "The Varuṇas and Sahadhammas,<br>the Accutas and Anejakas,";
M_LOC[1080] = "the Sūleyyas and Ruciras all came,";
M_LOC[1081] = "as did the Vāsavanesi gods.";
M_LOC[1082] = "These ten hosts of gods";
M_LOC[1083] = "shone in all different colors.";
M_LOC[1084] = "The Samānas, Mahāsamānas,<br>Mānusas, and Mānusuttamas all came,<br>and the gods depraved by play,";
M_LOC[1085] = "";
M_LOC[1086] = "Then came the Hari gods,<br>and the Lohitavāsīs.";
M_LOC[1087] = "The Pāragas and Mahāpāragas came,";
M_LOC[1088] = "such glorious gods.";
M_LOC[1089] = "These ten hosts of gods";
M_LOC[1090] = "shone in all different colors.";
M_LOC[1091] = "They’re powerful and brilliant,";
M_LOC[1092] = "And the Odātagayhas came as chiefs<br>of the Vicakkhaṇa gods.<br>The Sadāmattas and Hāragajas,";
M_LOC[1093] = "";
M_LOC[1094] = "Pajjuna came thundering,";
M_LOC[1095] = "he who rains on all quarters.";
M_LOC[1096] = "These ten hosts of gods";
M_LOC[1097] = "shone in all different colors.";
M_LOC[1098] = "They’re powerful and brilliant,";
M_LOC[1099] = "The Lambītakas, Lāmaseṭṭhas,<br>those called the Jotis and Āsavas.";
M_LOC[1100] = "The Gods Who Love to Create came too,";
M_LOC[1101] = "and those who delight in the Creations of Others.";
M_LOC[1102] = "These ten hosts of gods";
M_LOC[1103] = "shone in all different colors.";
M_LOC[1104] = "They’re powerful and brilliant,";
M_LOC[1105] = "so beautiful and glorious.";
M_LOC[1106] = "Rejoicing, they’ve come forth";
M_LOC[1107] = "and the dragon who brought them across,";
M_LOC[1108] = "who like the Moon has overcome darkness.’";
M_LOC[1109] = "Sanaṅkumāra and Tissa<br>also came to the meeting in the wood.<br>Of a thousand Brahmā realms,";
M_LOC[1110] = "";
M_LOC[1111] = "He has arisen, resplendent,<br>his formidable body so glorious.";
M_LOC[1112] = "The ten Issarās came there,<br>each one of them wielding power,";
M_LOC[1113] = "and in the middle of them came<br>Hārita with his following.”";
M_LOC[1114] = "When they had all come forth—<br>the gods with their Lord, and the Brahmās—";
M_LOC[1115] = "Māra’s army came forth too:<br>see the stupidity of the Dark Lord!<br>“Come, seize them and bind them,” he said,";
M_LOC[1116] = "";
M_LOC[1117] = "Surround them on all sides,<br>don’t let any escape!”<br>And so there the great general";
M_LOC[1118] = "";
M_LOC[1119] = "He struck the ground with his fist<br>to make a horrifying sound";
M_LOC[1120] = "like a storm cloud shedding rain,<br>thundering and flashing.";
M_LOC[1121] = "But then he retreated,";
M_LOC[1122] = "furious, out of control.";
M_LOC[1123] = "And all that was known";
M_LOC[1124] = "“Māra’s army has arrived;<br>mendicants, you should be aware of them.”<br>Those monks became keen,";
M_LOC[1125] = "";
M_LOC[1126] = "The army fled from those free of passion,<br>and not a single hair was stirred!";
M_LOC[1127] = "“All are triumphant in battle,<br>so fearless and glorious.";
M_LOC[1128] = "They rejoice with all the spirits,";
M_LOC[1129] = "the disciples well-known among men.”";
M_LOC[1130] = "Long Discourses 21<br>Sakka’s Questions<br>So I have heard.";
M_LOC[1131] = "";
M_LOC[1132] = "";
M_LOC[1133] = "";
M_LOC[1134] = "";
M_LOC[1135] = "";
M_LOC[1136] = "";
M_LOC[1137] = "";
M_LOC[1138] = "";
M_LOC[1139] = "As sweet as a breeze to one who’s sweating,<br>or when thirsty, a sweet and cooling drink,";
M_LOC[1140] = "so dear is your shining beauty to me,<br>just like the teaching is to all the saints!<br>Like a cure when you’re struck by fever dire,";
M_LOC[1141] = "";
M_LOC[1142] = "come on, darling, please put out my fire,<br>quench me like water on a flame.<br>As elephants burning in the heat of summer,";
M_LOC[1143] = "";
M_LOC[1144] = "so cool, full of petals and of pollen—<br>that’s how I would plunge into your breast.";
M_LOC[1145] = "Like elephants bursting bonds in rutting season,<br>beating off the pricks of lance and pikes—";
M_LOC[1146] = "I just don’t understand what is the reason<br>I’m so crazy for your shapely thighs!<br>For you, my heart is full of passion,";
M_LOC[1147] = "";
M_LOC[1148] = "There is no going back, I’m just not able,<br>I’m like a fish that’s hooked up on the line.";
M_LOC[1149] = "Come on, my darling, hold me, fair of thighs!<br>Embrace me, with your so bashful eyes!";
M_LOC[1150] = "Take me in your arms, my lovely lady,<br>that’s all I’d ever want or could desire.";
M_LOC[1151] = "Ah, then my desire was such a small thing,<br>my sweet, with your curling wavy hair;";
M_LOC[1152] = "now, like to arahants an offering,<br>it’s grown so very much from there.";
M_LOC[1153] = "Whatever the merit I have forged";
M_LOC[1154] = "by giving to such perfected beings—";
M_LOC[1155] = "may that, my altogether gorgeous,";
M_LOC[1156] = "ripen in togetherness with you.";
M_LOC[1157] = "Absorbed, the Sakyan meditates,<br>unified, alert, and mindful,<br>the sage aims right at the deathless state—";
M_LOC[1158] = "";
M_LOC[1159] = "And just like the sage would be rejoicing,<br>were he to awaken to the truth,";
M_LOC[1160] = "so I’d be rejoicing, lady,<br>were I to end up as one with you.";
M_LOC[1161] = "If Sakka were to grant me just one wish,<br>as Lord of the holy Thirty-Three,";
M_LOC[1162] = "my darling, you’re the only one I’d wish for,";
M_LOC[1163] = "so strong is the love I hold for you.";
M_LOC[1164] = "";
M_LOC[1165] = "";
M_LOC[1166] = "";
M_LOC[1167] = "";
M_LOC[1168] = "Like a freshly blossoming sal tree";
M_LOC[1169] = "is your father, my lady so wise.";
M_LOC[1170] = "I pay homage to him, bowing down humbly,";
M_LOC[1171] = "to he whose daughter is of such a kind.”";
M_LOC[1172] = "When Pañcasikha had spoken, the Buddha said to him,";
M_LOC[1173] = "For that is how the Realized Ones salute such illustrious spirits.";
M_LOC[1174] = "And being saluted by the Buddha, Sakka entered the Indasāla cave, bowed to the Buddha, and stood to one side.";
M_LOC[1175] = "And the gods of the Thirty-Three did likewise,";
M_LOC[1176] = "as did Pañcasikha.";
M_LOC[1177] = "And at that time the uneven places were evened out, the cramped places were opened up, the darkness vanished and light appeared, as happens through the glory of the gods.";
M_LOC[1178] = "‘I was a laywoman disciple of the seer,";
M_LOC[1179] = "and my name was Gopikā.";
M_LOC[1180] = "I was devoted to the Buddha and the teaching,";
M_LOC[1181] = "and I faithfully served the Saṅgha.";
M_LOC[1182] = "Because of the excellence of the Buddha’s teaching,";
M_LOC[1183] = "I’m now a mighty, splendid son of Sakka,";
M_LOC[1184] = "reborn among the Three and Thirty.";
M_LOC[1185] = "And here they know me as Gopaka.";
M_LOC[1186] = "Then I saw some mendicants who I’d seen before,";
M_LOC[1187] = "dwelling in the host of fairies.";
M_LOC[1188] = "When I used to be a human,";
M_LOC[1189] = "they were disciples of Gotama.";
M_LOC[1190] = "I served them with food and drink,";
M_LOC[1191] = "and clasped their feet in my own home.";
M_LOC[1192] = "Where on earth were they at";
M_LOC[1193] = "when they learned the Buddha’s teachings?";
M_LOC[1194] = "For each must know for themselves the teaching";
M_LOC[1195] = "so well-taught, realized by the seer.";
M_LOC[1196] = "I was one who followed you,";
M_LOC[1197] = "having heard the fine words of the noble ones.";
M_LOC[1198] = "I’m now a mighty, splendid son of Sakka,";
M_LOC[1199] = "reborn among the Three and Thirty.";
M_LOC[1200] = "But you followed the best of men,";
M_LOC[1201] = "and led the supreme spiritual life,";
M_LOC[1202] = "but still you’re born in this lesser realm,";
M_LOC[1203] = "a rebirth not befitting.";
M_LOC[1204] = "It’s a sorry sight I see, good sirs,";
M_LOC[1205] = "fellow Buddhists in a lesser realm.";
M_LOC[1206] = "Reborn in the host of fairies,";
M_LOC[1207] = "you only wait upon the gods.";
M_LOC[1208] = "Meanwhile, I dwelt in a house—";
M_LOC[1209] = "but see my distinction now!";
M_LOC[1210] = "Having been a woman now I’m a male god,";
M_LOC[1211] = "blessed with heavenly sensual pleasures.’";
M_LOC[1212] = "Scolded by that disciple of Gotama,";
M_LOC[1213] = "when they understood Gopaka, they were struck with urgency.";
M_LOC[1214] = "‘Let’s strive, let’s try hard—";
M_LOC[1215] = "we won’t serve others any more!’";
M_LOC[1216] = "Two of them aroused energy,";
M_LOC[1217] = "recalling the Buddha’s instructions.";
M_LOC[1218] = "Right away they became dispassionate,";
M_LOC[1219] = "seeing the drawbacks in sensual pleasures.";
M_LOC[1220] = "The fetters and bonds of sensual pleasures—";
M_LOC[1221] = "the ties of the Wicked One so hard to break—";
M_LOC[1222] = "they burst them like a bull elephant his ropes,";
M_LOC[1223] = "and passed right over the Thirty-Three.";
M_LOC[1224] = "The gods with Inda and Pajāpati";
M_LOC[1225] = "were all gathered in the Hall of Justice.";
M_LOC[1226] = "As they sat there, they passed over them,";
M_LOC[1227] = "the heroes desireless, practicing purity.";
M_LOC[1228] = "Seeing them, Vāsava was struck with a sense of urgency;";
M_LOC[1229] = "the master of gods in the midst of the group said,";
M_LOC[1230] = "‘These were born in the lesser fairy realm,";
M_LOC[1231] = "but now they pass us by!’";
M_LOC[1232] = "Heeding the speech of one so moved,";
M_LOC[1233] = "Gopaka addressed Vāsava,";
M_LOC[1234] = "‘There is a Buddha, a lord of men, in the world.";
M_LOC[1235] = "Known as the Sakyan Sage, he’s mastered the senses.";
M_LOC[1236] = "Those sons of his were bereft of mindfulness;";
M_LOC[1237] = "but when scolded by me they gained it back.";
M_LOC[1238] = "Of the three, there is one who remains";
M_LOC[1239] = "dwelling in the host of fairies.";
M_LOC[1240] = "But two, recollecting the path to awakening,";
M_LOC[1241] = "serene, spurn even the gods.’";
M_LOC[1242] = "The teaching’s explained in such a way";
M_LOC[1243] = "that not a single disciple doubts it.";
M_LOC[1244] = "We venerate the Buddha, the victor, lord of men,";
M_LOC[1245] = "who has crossed the flood and cut off doubt.";
M_LOC[1246] = "They attained to distinction fitting";
M_LOC[1247] = "the extent to which they understood the teaching here.";
M_LOC[1248] = "Two of them mastered the distinction of";
M_LOC[1249] = "the host of Brahmā’s Ministers.";
M_LOC[1250] = "We have come here, dear sir,";
M_LOC[1251] = "to realize this same teaching.";
M_LOC[1252] = "If the Buddha would give me a chance,";
M_LOC[1253] = "I would ask a question, dear sir.”";
M_LOC[1254] = "Then the Buddha thought,";
M_LOC[1255] = "“For a long time now this spirit has led a pure life. Any question he asks me will be beneficial, not useless.";
M_LOC[1256] = "And he will quickly understand any answer I give to his question.”";
M_LOC[1257] = "I’ll solve each and every<br>problem you have.”";
M_LOC[1258] = "The first recitation section is finished.";
M_LOC[1259] = "Having been granted an opportunity by the Buddha, Sakka asked the first question.";
M_LOC[1260] = "“Dear sir, what fetters bind the gods, humans, demons, dragons, fairies—and any of the other diverse creatures—";
M_LOC[1261] = "so that, though they wish to be free of enmity, violence, hostility, and hate, they still have enmity, violence, hostility, and hate?”";
M_LOC[1262] = "Such was Sakka’s question to the Buddha.";
M_LOC[1263] = "And the Buddha answered him:";
M_LOC[1264] = "“Lord of gods, the fetters of jealousy and stinginess bind the gods, humans, demons, dragons, fairies—and any of the other diverse creatures—";
M_LOC[1265] = "so that, though they wish to be free of enmity, violence, hostility, and hate, they still have enmity, violence, hostility, and hate.”";
M_LOC[1266] = "Such was the Buddha’s answer to Sakka.";
M_LOC[1267] = "Delighted, Sakka approved and agreed with what the Buddha said, saying,";
M_LOC[1268] = "“That’s so true, Blessed One! That’s so true, Holy One!";
M_LOC[1269] = "Hearing the Buddha’s answer, I’ve gone beyond doubt and got rid of indecision.”";
M_LOC[1270] = "And then, having approved and agreed with what the Buddha said, Sakka asked another question:";
M_LOC[1271] = "“But dear sir, what is the source, origin, birthplace, and inception of jealousy and stinginess?";
M_LOC[1272] = "";
M_LOC[1273] = "";
M_LOC[1274] = "";
M_LOC[1275] = "";
M_LOC[1276] = "";
M_LOC[1277] = "";
M_LOC[1278] = "";
M_LOC[1279] = "";
M_LOC[1280] = "";
M_LOC[1281] = "";
M_LOC[1282] = "";
M_LOC[1283] = "";
M_LOC[1284] = "";
M_LOC[1285] = "";
M_LOC[1286] = "Sir, that’s how I understand the detailed meaning of the Buddha’s brief statement.";
M_LOC[1287] = "Hearing the Buddha’s answer, I’ve gone beyond doubt and got rid of indecision.”";
M_LOC[1288] = "And then Sakka asked another question:";
M_LOC[1289] = "“Dear sir, do all ascetics and brahmins have the same doctrine, ethics, desires, and attachments?”";
M_LOC[1290] = "“No, lord of gods, they do not.”";
M_LOC[1291] = "“Why not?”";
M_LOC[1292] = "“The world has many and diverse elements.";
M_LOC[1293] = "Whatever element sentient beings insist on in this world of many and diverse elements, they obstinately stick to it, insisting that:";
M_LOC[1294] = "‘This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.’";
M_LOC[1295] = "That’s why not all ascetics and brahmins have the same doctrine, ethics, desires, and attachments.”";
M_LOC[1296] = "“Dear sir, have all ascetics and brahmins reached the ultimate end, the ultimate sanctuary, the ultimate spiritual life, the ultimate goal?”";
M_LOC[1297] = "“No, lord of gods, they have not.”";
M_LOC[1298] = "“Why not?”";
M_LOC[1299] = "“Those mendicants who are freed through the ending of craving have reached the ultimate end, the ultimate sanctuary, the ultimate spiritual life, the ultimate goal.";
M_LOC[1300] = "That’s why not all ascetics and brahmins have reached the ultimate end, the ultimate sanctuary, the ultimate spiritual life, the ultimate goal.”";
M_LOC[1301] = "I have gained an extended life:";
M_LOC[1302] = "know this, dear sir.";
M_LOC[1303] = "When I fall from the heavenly host,<br>leaving behind the non-human life,";
M_LOC[1304] = "I shall consciously go to a new womb,<br>wherever my mind delights.";
M_LOC[1305] = "This is the second reason.<br>Living happily under the guidance";
M_LOC[1306] = "";
M_LOC[1307] = "I shall practice according to method,<br>aware and mindful.";
M_LOC[1308] = "This is the third reason.";
M_LOC[1309] = "And if awakening should arise<br>as I practice according to the method,";
M_LOC[1310] = "I shall live as one who understands,<br>and my end shall come right there.";
M_LOC[1311] = "This is the fourth reason.";
M_LOC[1312] = "When I fall from the human realm,<br>leaving behind the human life,";
M_LOC[1313] = "I shall become a god again,<br>in the supreme heaven realm.";
M_LOC[1314] = "This is the fifth reason.<br>They are the finest of gods,";
M_LOC[1315] = "";
M_LOC[1316] = "So long as my final life goes on,";
M_LOC[1317] = "there my home will be.";
M_LOC[1318] = "Seeing these six reasons I speak of such joy and happiness.";
M_LOC[1319] = "My wishes unfulfilled,<br>doubting and undecided,";
M_LOC[1320] = "I wandered for such a long time,<br>in search of the Realized One.";
M_LOC[1321] = "I imagined that ascetics<br>living in seclusion";
M_LOC[1322] = "must surely be awakened,<br>so I went to sit near them.";
M_LOC[1323] = "‘How is there success?<br>How is there failure?’<br>But they couldn’t answer such questions";
M_LOC[1324] = "";
M_LOC[1325] = "And when they found out that I<br>was Sakka, come from the gods,";
M_LOC[1326] = "they questioned me instead about<br>the deed that brought me to this state.";
M_LOC[1327] = "I taught them the Dhamma<br>as I had learned it among men.";
M_LOC[1328] = "They were delighted with that, saying:<br>‘We’ve seen Vāsava!’";
M_LOC[1329] = "Now since I’ve seen the Buddha,<br>who helps us overcome doubt,";
M_LOC[1330] = "today, free of fear,<br>I pay homage to the awakened one.";
M_LOC[1331] = "Destroyer of the dart of craving,<br>the Buddha is unrivaled.<br>I bow to the great hero,";
M_LOC[1332] = "";
M_LOC[1333] = "";
M_LOC[1334] = "";
M_LOC[1335] = "";
M_LOC[1336] = "In the world with its gods,<br>there is no-one like you.”<br>Then Sakka addressed the fairy Pañcasikha,<br>“Dear Pañcasikha, you were very helpful to me, since you first charmed the Buddha,";
M_LOC[1337] = "";
M_LOC[1338] = "";
